response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Counting Words\", \"description\": \"Write a function `count_words` that takes as input a string and returns the number of words in that string.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef count_words(s: str) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing one or more words.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the number of words in the input string.\", \"code\": \"def count_words(s: str) -> int:\\n    return len(s.split())\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert count_words('Hello, World!') == 2\", \"assert count_words('This is a test string.') == 5\", \"assert count_words('   ') == 0\", \"assert count_words('One word only...') == 1\"] }"
